<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="3974" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[430,920,567,623]" box="[590,720,599,623]" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">
(
<figureCitation box="[598,711,599,623]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-164@24.[138,1186,932,1575]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 10. Phortica pangi Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">Figure 10</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,243,679,703]" box="[138,243,679,703]" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">
<emphasis box="[138,243,679,703]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,1185,727,879]" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">
Paramere apically with one sensillum, two small teeth and a small triangular, lobe-shaped process (
<figureCitation box="[249,386,759,783]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-164@24.[138,1186,932,1575]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 10. Phortica pangi Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">Figure 10C</figureCitation>
); branch of aedeagal basal bridge large quadripartite, strongly sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[277,414,791,815]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-164@24.[138,1186,932,1575]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 10. Phortica pangi Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">Figure 10C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,1185,727,879]" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">
Some characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen, 2005" authorityName="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[612,745,823,847]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uncinata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[612,745,823,847]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">P. uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[759,857,823,847]" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are not referred to in the following description.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973" startId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" targetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" targetPageId="24">
<paragraph blockId="24.[138,1185,1611,1683]" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">
Figure 10. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen and Wen" authorityName="Chen and Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[244,516,1611,1630]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[244,369,1611,1630]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">Phortica pangi</emphasis>
Chen and Wen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[524,600,1611,1630]" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis box="[608,622,1612,1631]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="3973">„</emphasis>
. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="25.[125,245,137,161]" box="[125,245,137,161]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
<emphasis box="[125,245,137,161]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[125,1007,185,209]" box="[125,1007,185,209]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
<emphasis box="[125,194,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Head.</emphasis>
Frons dark brown. Face brown. Gena dark brown. Postgena brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[125,618,256,280]" box="[125,618,256,280]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
<emphasis box="[125,214,256,280]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Thorax.</emphasis>
Anepisternum with a few setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[125,1042,326,350]" box="[125,1042,326,350]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
<emphasis box="[125,183,326,349]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Legs.</emphasis>
Mid tibia subapically with three to four longer setae on anterior surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[125,1172,398,455]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
<emphasis box="[125,236,398,422]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Abdominal third and fifth tergites with medially and laterally interrupted, broad, brown bands along posterior margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[125,1172,501,654]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
<emphasis box="[125,311,501,525]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium pubescent, with six setae near dorsal and posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[133,270,533,557]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-164@24.[138,1186,932,1575]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 10. Phortica pangi Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with about six to eight long setae on basal one-third, and a few short setae on distal two-thirds, and about ten prensisetae along inner margin (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1159,566,590]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-164@24.[138,1186,932,1575]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 10. Phortica pangi Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Figure 10A</figureCitation>
). Paramere lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[490,627,598,622]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-164@24.[138,1186,932,1575]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 10. Phortica pangi Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Figure 10C</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal median rod subapically expanded, symmetrical, with one pair of processes (
<figureCitation box="[603,740,630,654]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="24.[138,198,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[139,1185,933,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-164@24.[138,1186,932,1575]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figure 10. Phortica pangi Chen and Wen, sp. nov., „. (A) Epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (B) 10th sternite and additional plate (frontal view); (C) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal median rod (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5221196" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5221196/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Figure 10C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
