<paragraph blockId="25.[125,220,1256,1280]" box="[125,220,1256,1280]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
<emphasis box="[125,220,1256,1280]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[125,1172,1305,1394]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen, 2005" authorityName="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[434,573,1305,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setitabula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[434,573,1305,1329]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">P. setitabula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[584,679,1305,1329]" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the paramere lacking pubescence and the aedeagal median rod subapically symmetrical. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Gao &amp; Wen" authorityYear="2005" box="[776,916,1337,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setitabula">
<emphasis box="[776,916,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="3974">P. setitabula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the arista is without ventral branches; additional plate between cerci very large, more than tenth sternite.
</paragraph>
